M. F. O’DEA, Appellant, v. Harry J. EDWARDS, Trustee in Bankruptcy of Empire Finance Company, a Corporation, Bankrupt, and Mortgage Guarantee Company, Appellees. No. 6845. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 14, 1933. Courtney L. Moore and Sterling Carr, both of San Francisco, Cal., for appellant. Ernest J. Torregano, Oliver Dibble, and Kimball Dyer, all of San Francisco, Cal., for appellees.

Before WILBUR, SAWTELLE, and MACK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed, each party to pay its own costs; mandate forthwith.
